com.digi.xbee.api.connection.android

Interface AndroidUSBPermissionListener


  • public interface AndroidUSBPermissionListener
    This interface is used as a listener to wait for user permissions after a USB access request is sent in Android.

    Permissions can be granted or denied, the result is passed within the {permissionReceived(boolean) method to the class implementing it.

    Since:
    1.2.0

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      void permissionReceived(boolean permissionGranted)
      This method is called whenever the USB Permissions request answer is received from the user.
